flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: NPI program launch event or updated launch volume/target recorded in SAP S/4HANA (or scheduled ramp planning cadence).]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers + STREAMS - Ingest master and transactional NPI inputs from SAP, MES and supplier systems; run data quality checks and standardize schemas.]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: STREAMS - Subject Areas - Transform and assemble planning subject area for ramp modeling (plant-line-sku-timebucket facts, constraints, cost parameters).]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Remote Functions (optimizer) - Execute deterministic optimizer (sequencing, capacity allocation, supplier allocations, cost minimization) with business constraints and scenario variants.]
  N3 --> N4{PB: Process Builder + CWB Lifecycle + UI Screen - Present recommended ramp plan and key KPIs to launch stakeholders for review and accept/request changes via a CWB review workbench.}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[PB: Remote Functions (ERP writeback) - Apply approved plan: write production orders, push schedule and component releases back to SAP S/4HANA and notify suppliers of commit windows.]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Notification + UI Screen (dashboard) - Surface launch KPIs (OTIF, COGS delta, working capital impact, ramp adherence) and alert owners on deviations for ongoing monitoring.]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Automated, validated ramp plans executed in SAP: reduced COGS from optimized allocations, faster time-to-market through coordinated sequencing, improved OTIF for launch SKUs, and reduced working capital via staged inventory and supplier synchronization.]
  N4 -->|Stakeholders approve recommended plan| B1[Process Builder proceeds to ERP writeback and supplier notifications; schedule locked for execution.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Plan executed; monitoring begins and KPIs tracked in Subject Areas]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Stakeholders request changes or tight...| B2[CWB Lifecycle routes inputs/overrides back to Process Builder which re-invokes Remote Functions optimizer with updated constraints and generates new plan variant.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Re-optimized plan produced and re-presented for approval (iterative loop until acceptance)]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Critical data quality or missing supp...| B3[Process Builder triggers Data Quality & Validation tasks in STREAMS, sends notifications to data owners and pauses decision until resolved.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Ingestion paused and decision deferred until trusted inputs are available; prevents flawed plan execution]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]